salixDsx0MIB.name: salixDsx0MIB
salixDsx0MIB.contactinfo: 904 Wind River Lane Suite 101 Gaithersburg, MD 20878 (301)-417-0017
salixDsx0MIB.description: The MIB describing SALIX specific DS0 objects

salixDsx0CrossConnectTable.name: salixDsx0CrossConnectTable
salixDsx0CrossConnectTable.description: The table that describes the active DS0 Cross Connections on the system. There should be one entry for each active Cross Connect on the system.

salixDsx0CrossConnectEntry.name: salixDsx0CrossConnectEntry
salixDsx0CrossConnectEntry.description: An entry in the ITX DS0 cross connect table. This entry describes the status of the DS0 cross connect, and also provides information describing the cross connect

salixDsx0CrossConnectHighInterface.name: salixDsx0CrossConnectHighInterface
salixDsx0CrossConnectHighInterface.description: The high ifIndex for identifying the cross connect. Identifies the DS0 Channel involved in the cross connect. The salixDsx0CrossConnectHighInterface value should be higher than the salixDsx0CrossConnectLowInterface value

salixDsx0CrossConnectLowInterface.name: salixDsx0CrossConnectLowInterface
salixDsx0CrossConnectLowInterface.description: The low ifIndex for identifying the cross connect. Identifies the DS0 Channel involved in the cross connect. The salixDsx0CrossConnectLowInterface value should be lower than the salixDsx0CrossConnectHighInterface value

salixDsx0CrossConnectDirection.name: salixDsx0CrossConnectDirection
salixDsx0CrossConnectDirection.description: This attribute describes the direction of traffic flow the DS0 cross connect. high2low(1) - Traffic flows from the high interface to the low interface in the cross connect low2high(2) - Traffic flows from the low interface to the high interface in the cross connect bidirectional(3) - Traffic flows both directions through the cross connect

salixDsx0CrossConnectOperStatus.name: salixDsx0CrossConnectOperStatus
salixDsx0CrossConnectOperStatus.description: This attribute indicates the operational state of the DS0 cross connection. up(1) - The cross connect is up and active down(2) - The cross connect is down and no traffic is passing unknown(3) - The status of the cross connect is not know

salixDsx0CrossConnectStartTime.name: salixDsx0CrossConnectStartTime
salixDsx0CrossConnectStartTime.description: The time at which the cross connect was created

salixDsx0CrossConnectRowStatus.name: salixDsx0CrossConnectRowStatus
salixDsx0CrossConnectRowStatus.description: The status of this entry in the salixDsx0CrossConnectTable. This object is used to delete a salixDsx0CrossConnectTable entry. To destroy a cross connect, set this value to destory(6) Row status values: active(1) - set by the agent after this entry is created notInService(2) - not applicable notReady(3) - not applicable createAndGo(4) - not applicable createAndWait(5)- not applicable destroy(6) - set by the management entity to destroy entry

salixDsx0ConfigTable.name: salixDsx0ConfigTable
salixDsx0ConfigTable.description: The DS0 Configuration table. Augments the DS0 Configuration table from the DS0-MIB. There is an entry in this table for each DS0 interface.

salixDsx0ConfigEntry.name: salixDsx0ConfigEntry
salixDsx0ConfigEntry.description: An augmented entry in the DS0 Configuration table. There is an entry in this table for each DS0 interface.

salixDsx0Status.name: salixDsx0Status
salixDsx0Status.description: Indicated the status of the given DS0 notused(1) - The DS0 is not currently being used crossconnect(2) - The DS0 is currently cross connected rtpconnect(3) - The DS0 is currently connect to an RTP session loopback(4) - The DS0 is currently being looped back test(5) - The DS0 is currently being continuity tested unknown(6) - The status of the DS0 is not known

salixDsx0Group.name: salixDsx0Group
salixDsx0Group.description: Additional salix specific objects for connections

salixDsx0Compliance.name: salixDsx0Compliance
salixDsx0Compliance.description: The basic implementation requirements for the SALIX-DS0-MIB.
